{"id":"ev_eb67702372fd4188","runId":"run_297","type":"delegation","at":1782821591241,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_60f746ce938241b3","atom":0,"task":"Revise the governance doc cocoder/standards/test-architecture.md to close the two gaps named in ticket 0089 (cocoder/tickets/open/0089-test-architecture-standard-adaptability-on-repo-takeover.md). This is a documentation-only edit to that ONE file. Read the ticket and the current standard first.\n\nGAP 1 — make the rule phrasing language-neutral (today it is implicitly TypeScript/JS-shaped):\n- Rule 1: '*.test.ts file' -> phrase framework-agnostically: one cohesive behavior area per test file, using whatever the repo's test-file convention is; keep '*.test.ts' only as a parenthetical example.\n- Rule 2: 'a single co-located *-support.ts module' -> 'a single co-located shared-fixtures module in the repo's own language' (keep *-support.ts as the TS/JS example). The single-owner / never-copy-a-fixture rule stays.\n- Rule 3: 'describe label' -> a descriptive grouping/label that names the behavior area (describe(...) as the JS example).\n- Rule 4: keep the ~600-line / ~25-test soft budget as a concrete default, but state the budget is expressed in the repo's own terms (lines/tests/whatever the language idioms use); it stays a soft split-prompt, not a hard cap.\nThe four rules must remain four rules with the same intent — generalize wording only, do not drop or weaken any rule.\n\nGAP 2 — strengthen the 'Existing Repos' clause from the current stub into a real detect-and-honor posture:\n- On takeover, CoCoder DETECTS and HONORS the repo's established test framework, directory layout, and naming rather than rewriting to CoCoder's structure (ties to the shared standards: match surrounding style, preserve unrelated work, touch only what the task requires).\n- The standard is the DEFAULT for new test work and a CONVERGENCE TARGET over time — never a forced top-down migration of a working layout.\n- Where an existing layout is actively harmful (e.g. a multi-thousand-line test monolith, as CoCoder's own runner.test.ts was before run_294), CoCoder PROPOSES an opt-in split, not an imposed rewrite.\n- Remove the now-stale forward-pointer sentence 'Deeper detection and honoring of a taken-over repo's conventions is tracked in ticket 0089.' since this edit IS that work. (A per-root convention-profile captured by the onboard-existing recon flow is a separate code follow-up, not part of this doc edit — do NOT touch any code or recon files.)\n\nACCEPTANCE: both gaps closed in cocoder/standards/test-architecture.md only; rules read framework-agnostic with TS/JS shown as examples not requirements; the Existing Repos section states detect-and-honor + default-for-new + convergence-target + propose-opt-in-split-when-harmful. MUST NOT break: keep the 'Tests never live inside [root]/cocoder/' Test Location rule, keep the Dogfooding section and the run_294 worked-example facts (5,638 lines -> 17 files + one runner.test-support.ts, 741 tests green) intact and accurate. Do not edit any other file (not the ticket, not code, not recon). Match the doc's existing terse prose style."}}
